ay be rare, the fact that\nnearly 100\\% remain bound implies they may play an important role in the\ncompact merger rate, important for gravitational waves (GWs) that, in turn, can\nproduce a new class of ultrashort GRBs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 May 2015 21:29:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Nov 2015 15:04:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-09"}
