s to be seen whether this or other baryonic\nphysics can explain the observed rotation curves of the entire population of\ndwarf and low surface brightness galaxies. If not, perhaps more complicated\nphysics such as self-interacting dark matter may be needed. But standard LCDM\nappears to be successful in predicting the dark matter halo substructure that\nis now observed via gravitational lensing and breaks in cold stellar streams,\nand any alternative theory must do at least as well.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 May 2015 22:14:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
