{"id":"1505.03321","submitter":"Ignacio Zurri\\'an","authors":"Ignacio Zurri\\'an","title":"The Algebra of Differential Operators for a Gegenbauer Weight Matrix","comments":null,"journal-ref":"International mathematics research notices, Vol. 2016, No. 00, pp.\n  1--29","doi":"10.1093/imrn/rnw104","report-no":null,"categories":"math.CA math.RT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper we study in detail algebraic properties of the algebra\n$\\mathcal D(W)$ of differential operators associated to a matrix weight of\nGegenbauer type. We prove that two second order operators generate the algebra,\nindeed $\\mathcal D(W)$ is isomorphic to the free algebra generated by two\nelements subject to certain relations. Also, the center is isomorphic to the\naffine algebra of a singular rational curve. The algebra $\\mathcal D(W)$ is a\nfinitely-generated torsion-free module over its center, but it is not flat and\ntherefore it is not projective.\n  This is the second detailed study of an algebra $\\mathcal D(W)$ and the first\none coming from spherical functions and group representations. We prove that\nthe algebras for different Gegenbauer weights and the algebras studied\npreviously, related to Hermite weights, are isomorphic to each other. We give\nsome general results that allow us to regard the algebra $\\mathcal D(W)$ as the\ncentralizer of its center in the Weyl algebra. We do believe that this should\nhold for any irreducible weight and the case considered in this paper\nrepresents a good step in this direction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 May 2015 17:06:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 15 May 2015 00:45:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 30 Dec 2015 20:00:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-01"}
